ized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Néill</b> ‘descendant of <i>Niall</i>’, an Irish personal name possibly derived from <i>néal</i> ‘cloud’ (see   Neil  ).","History: Bearers of this surname mostly claim descent from Niall Noígíallach (Niall of the Nine Hostages), a legendary king of Ireland who flourished in the 5th century. His descendants, the Ui Neill dynasty, dominated Ireland, on and off, from the 6th to the 10th century. The surname itself can be traced with some confidence to one of these descendants, namely Niall Glúndubh mac Aodha (died 919), High King of Ireland from 911 to 919, with a power base in Tyrone, Ulster."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"O'Nell was born about 0970, in Scotland. She had at least 1 daughter with Cornic \"Airt vic Chuinn Cheudchathchich\" O'Nell."},"et":{"about 0970–":"umbes 0970–Surnud","0960–Male":"0960–Surnud","0990–1078":"0990–1078","0970–Female":"0970–Surnud","0970":"0970","0960":"0960","0990":"0990","1078":"1078","about 0970":"umbes 0970","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochawe, Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 0970–":"noin 0970–Kuollut","0960–Male":"0960–Kuollut","0990–1078":"0990–1078","0970–Female":"0970–Kuollut","0970":"0970","0960":"0960","0990":"0990","1078":"1078","about 0970":"noin 0970","Scotland":"Scotland","Lochawe, Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 0970–":"environ 0970–Décédée","0960–Male":"0960–Décédé","0990–1078":"0990–1078","0970–Female":"0970–Décédée","0970":"0970","0960":"0960","0990":"0990","1078":"1078","about 0970":"environ 0970","Scotland":"Écosse","Lochawe, Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Lochawe, Argyll, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"O'Nell est née environ 0970, à Écosse. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Cornic \"Airt vic Chuinn Cheudchathchich\" O'Nell."},"de":{"about 0970–":"um 0970–Verstorben","0960–Male":"0960–Verstorben","0990–1078":"0990–1078","0970–Female":"0970–Verstorben","0970":"0970","0960":"0960","0990":"0990"